Final file:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

public static class NativeCompression
{
    [DllImport("compresslib", EntryPoint = "compress_buffer",
        CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl, ExactSpelling = true)]
    public static extern int CompressBuffer(
        byte[] input,
        UIntPtr inputLen,
        byte[] output,
        UIntPtr outputLen,
        out UIntPtr bytesWritten);
}
```

Key choices:
- **`EntryPoint`** maps the C# name `CompressBuffer` to the native `compress_buffer`.
- **`UIntPtr`** correctly represents `size_t` on x86 (4 bytes) and stays portable.
- **`Cdecl`** matches the default C calling convention.
